[John Horton Conway](https://www.quantamagazine.org/john-conways-life-in-games-20150828/) died on 11 April 2020.
Prolific in many branches of mathematics, Conway was a professor at both Princeton University and Cambridge. Despite having an Erd√∂s number of one,  he is arguable most famous for his cellular automaton, [Conway's Game of Life](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conway%27s_Game_of_Life).
